Chatto Mixed License Notice

Chatto uses per-file SPDX license metadata following the REUSE specification.
The canonical license metadata is in REUSE.toml and in any SPDX headers or
adjacent .license files present in the source tree.

The default repository license is the GNU Affero General Public License
version 3 or any later version (AGPL-3.0-or-later). This covers the Chatto
server, CLI, frontend application, and release artifacts unless a more specific
license is declared.

Selected integration and documentation surfaces are licensed under the Apache
License 2.0 (Apache-2.0), including public protocol/API definitions, generated
TypeScript API client/types, documentation, and examples as annotated in
REUSE.toml.

The full license texts are available in:

- LICENSE-APACHE
- LICENSE-AGPL
- LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt
- LICENSES/AGPL-3.0-or-later.txt

See LICENSE.md for a human-readable overview of the license boundary.
